  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Manager- Mechanical Design",
  "description": "<p><strong>Candidate Profile:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree /Master's in Mechanical Engineering or a relevant discipline</li><li>10-15 years of working experience in automation machines design</li><li>Ability to communicate in Mandarin to work closely with colleagues in the China HQ</li><li>Strong technical background in semiconductor-related equipment development involving ultra-high precision, high-speed mechanisms</li><li>Possess good technical drawing skills using either Creo/SolidWorks</li><li>Knowledge in semiconductor packaging and assembly processes</li><li>Experienced as a Technical leader with good project management skills</li><li>Excellent systematic problem-solving ability using 8D report, Ishikawa, DIVE or other tools</li><li>Good leadership abilities and able to coach, motivate & guide direct reports, including conflict resolution</li></ul><p><strong>Core Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><strong>Leadership & Product Development</strong></p><ul><li>Leading design engineering teams through the complete product lifecycle, from individual modules to full machine systems</li><li>Driving continuous improvement programs (CIP) to extend product viability and boost profitability</li></ul><p><strong>Technical Execution</strong></p><ul><li>Conducting reliability and feasibility testing</li><li>Performing design and drawing reviews</li><li>Managing technical documentation and BOMs (Bill of Materials)</li></ul><p><strong>Cross-Functional Collaboration</strong></p><ul><li>Supporting sales teams with technical specifications, cost analysis, and product evaluations</li><li>Participating in project meetings with constructive input</li><li>Coordinating between Singapore and China manufacturing operations</li></ul><p><strong>Customer-Facing Technical Support</strong></p><ul><li>Resolving field issues and customer complaints</li><li>Taking ownership of product performance at customer sites</li><li>Handling both sales and service inquiries</li></ul><p><strong>Product Ownership</strong></p><ul><li>Specifically responsible for the mechanical aspects of sorters, laser marking, and scanning products post-R&D handover</li></ul>",
